# PROJECT RULES

## GENERAL
- All code must be written in English
- Use clean code principles
- Prefer readability over cleverness
- Avoid large components (>200 lines)

## STACK
- React (Vite)
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion
- Zustand

## ARCHITECTURE
- Use functional components only
- Separate logic into hooks
- Keep components presentational when possible
- Use absolute imports

## NAMING
- Components: PascalCase
- Hooks: useSomething
- Variables/functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_CASE

## STYLING
- Use Tailwind only
- Avoid inline styles
- Extract repeated patterns into components

## STATE
- Use Zustand for global state
- Avoid prop drilling

## PERFORMANCE
- Lazy load sections when possible
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders

## UX
- Always include hover and focus states
- Ensure accessibility (ARIA, keyboard nav)

## OUTPUT EXPECTATION
- Always explain briefly what was created
- Keep code clean and production-ready
